This product includes software originally developed by Luke Channings as
"MovieMatch" (https://github.com/LukeChannings/moviematch), licensed under the
Apache License, Version 2.0.

This distribution is a modified fork of that work. In accordance with section
4(b) of the License, notable changes from the original include:

  - Multi-user rooms: create or join a room with a short code; matched posters
    flip to reveal who voted; live occupancy with a name list; tap-to-copy code.
  - TV-show support (each series appears as a single swipeable card).
  - Per-room content filtering: allowed-library selection, minimum and maximum
    content-age dropdowns, and an include-unrated toggle.
  - "Open in Plex" action on matches, using the universal app.plex.tv deep link
    so it resolves to the correct movie or show on desktop and mobile.
  - Frosted-glass UI redesign, a custom colour palette, and the dumbbell-shaped
    room bar.

